Update failing background randomization test

after recent changes, given a default single background with multiple
decisions that can be randomized too. This change removes the restriction requiring a different background to be selected.

commit.message:
Remove unneeded test for background randomization

The test to check if a default single background wil be chosen again is
unnecessary and does not contribute towards testing behavior. Additionally, the Array filter method is not used anymore and a stub relied on it for the test. Backgrounds can now be reselected at random after recent changes, but with possibly different decisions. While the decision change can be tested, there is no comparison and the same decisions could be chosen (unlikely, but possible). This may be remodeled from a form's perspective to generate the possible form to fill out in advance. It can be done as a radio button list that populates on background selection within the same form instead of having separate forms per decision.
Use node 13.3.0 and yarn 1.21.0 in Travis

Allow random reselection of the same background

Given multiple decisions, allow for combinations where the background
has not changed, but the decisions potentially have. Default is 1
background with 1 decision (2 choices), so it's best to allow for switching
between the choices at first until the user adds custom backgrounds
(once available).

Reorganize class screen; fix state refresh bug

- Simplify class selection screen by simplifying state management and
using a map over an array for fast access per screen render
- Fix #30 issue by ignoring default state on screen rerender and adding
throttling for fast clicking the randomize button in the navigation for
class and background selection screens
- Create mock classes for use in testing
Update tests after upgrading dependencies to latest within current range
Fix current tests due to breaking changes with tests around themed components

Update expo SDK and project dependencies

- Update expo SDK to v35
- Ensure app runs again successfully via Expo
- Update Asset/Font to run by their new expo-* locations
- Make jest/babel changes to allow tests to run (pending snapshot fixes)
[Alpha] Commit recent changes for tests

Add character background test; separate Info files

- Complete test for character background.
- Separate Info config files to enable jest mocks of specific config
files. This allows testing all scenarios. For instance, character backgrounds can be mocked up to incorporate one background per test case instead of only using the default single background.
